{"id":53115,"title":"[Hypothyroidism after radiotherapy of the neck area: monitoring of thyroid function is important].","abstract":"We present three patients with primary hypothyroidism after previous radiotherapy of the neck area. Myxoedema coma occurred in one of these patients. Lifelong follow-up of thyroid function is recommended after radiotherapy of the neck. Monitoring of thyroid function should be performed at least once a year by the radiation oncologist or by the general practitioner. ","date":"2014-02-19","categories":"Endocrine System Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24548592","annotations":[{"name":"Hypothyroidism","weight":0.889548,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hypothyroidism"},{"name":"Radiation therapy","weight":0.822622,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy"},{"name":"Oncology","weight":0.760896,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oncology"},{"name":"Radiation","weight":0.667086,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation"},{"name":"Radiation oncologist","weight":0.567336,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_oncologist"},{"name":"General practitioner","weight":0.488649,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_practitioner"},{"name":"Coma","weight":0.458945,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coma"},{"name":"Thyroid","weight":0.186848,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thyroid"},{"name":"Neck","weight":0.0508378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neck"},{"name":"General officer","weight":0.0300804,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_officer"},{"name":"Myxedema","weight":0.0274275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myxedema"},{"name":"Obstetrics","weight":0.0226287,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obstetrics"},{"name":"Area","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area"},{"